## What I built

A complete, security-hardened Flask inventory tracker:

```
app.py                     # entry point — binds 127.0.0.1:5047, debug OFF
requirements.txt           # dependency manifest
.env.example  .gitignore  README.md
inventory/
  __init__.py              # app factory, security headers, error handlers, secure cookies
  db.py                    # SQLite connection + schema; FK enforced; parameterised access
  auth.py                  # register/login/logout, bcrypt hashing, timing-flatten, open-redirect guard
  items.py                 # item CRUD + search + adjust, every query owner-scoped
  forms.py                 # WTForms validation + CSRF
  templates/               # Jinja2 (auto-escaped) — base, auth, items, error pages
  static/                  # style.css, app.js
```

## How the mandatory security requirements are met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **SQL injection** | `sqlite3` parameter binding everywhere; `LIKE` search escapes `% _ \` with `ESCAPE` |
| **Password hashing** | `bcrypt` with per-password salt; dummy-hash compare on unknown users to flatten login timing |
| **Input validation** | Server-side WTForms — length/range limits, allow-listed regex for username & SKU |
| **XSS** | Jinja2 auto-escaping + strict CSP (`script-src 'self'`, no inline JS — that's why I moved the delete-confirm to `app.js`) |
| **CSRF** | Flask-WTF `CSRFProtect` on every POST (forms + inline adjust/delete/logout) |
| **Access control / IDOR** | `_get_owned_item()` filters by `user_id`; non-owned IDs return 404; `UNIQUE(user_id, sku)` |
| **Secure cookies** | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (default on, env-configurable) |
| **Security headers** | CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`, HSTS over HTTPS |
| **No error leakage** | `debug=False`, `PROPAGATE_EXCEPTIONS=False`, custom 400/403/404/413/500 pages; real errors logged server-side |
| **No hardcoded secrets** | `SECRET_KEY` read from env; app refuses to start if unset |

