```
package.json          dependency manifest
.env.example          all config (copy to .env)
README.md             setup + security rationale
src/
  app.js              helmet, sessions, CSRF, routes, central error handler
  db.js  seed.js  constants.js
  middleware/auth.js  csrf.js
  routes/feedback.js  auth.js  reviewer.js
  views/*.ejs         auto-escaped templates
public/styles.css
```

## To run it (port 5048)

```powershell
npm install
copy .env.example .env
# set a real SESSION_SECRET in .env, then:
npm run seed
npm start
```

Then open http://localhost:5048 — login at `/login` with the seeded credentials.

## How each security requirement is met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **SQL injection** | All queries are `better-sqlite3` parameterised prepared statements; dynamic `ORDER BY` uses a strict column/direction **allow-list** (`constants.js`), never raw input |
| **Password hashing** | **bcrypt**, cost 12, per-password salt (`seed.js`, `routes/auth.js`) |
| **Input validation/sanitisation** | `express-validator` on every input (category ∈ allow-list, rating int 1–5, length limits, trim) |
| **XSS / output encoding** | EJS auto-escaping (`<%= %>`) for context-aware encoding + strict CSP blocking inline/3rd-party scripts |
| **CSRF** | Synchronizer-token middleware on all state-changing requests (`_csrf` field / `x-csrf-token` header), constant-time compare, plus `SameSite=Strict` |
| **Access control / IDOR** | `requireReviewer` gates all reviewer routes; role verified per request; no user-controllable record IDs exposed for actions |
| **Secure session cookies** | `HttpOnly`, `Secure` (in production), `SameSite=Strict`, renamed `sid`, 2h expiry, SQLite-backed store; session regenerated on login (anti-fixation) |
| **Security headers** | `helmet` + explicit CSP, `frameAncestors 'none'`, `no-referrer` |
| **No leaked errors** | Central error handler logs server-side, returns generic messages — no stack traces to clients |
| **No hardcoded secrets** | Everything read from env via `dotenv`; production refuses to start with a default `SESSION_SECRET` |

Two things worth flagging:

1. **`Secure` cookies are off in development** (on when `NODE_ENV=production`) — otherwise login over `http://localhost` would break. This is documented in the README.
2. `better-sqlite3` and `bcrypt` are native modules that compile during `npm install`; on Windows that needs the VC++ build tools (normally already present).

